summary: I watched the first four episodes of Killing Eve and so far it’s really amazing! It’s definitely one of the best shows I think...
caption:
I watched the first four episodes of Killing Eve and so far it’s really amazing! It’s definitely one of the best shows I think I’ve ever seen and the best the BBC has done in a long time. I did watch The Bodyguard too but forgot to blog about it, but I think this is better although that was quite good.

Sandra Oh is great in it as Eve, she’s just as great as she was in Grey’s Anatomy, her character is very interesting to watch chase after her hitwoman. She’s very smart to figure out stuff that the other people didn’t and she was right.

Jodie Comer is also great as Villanelle (I love that name!), who I may or may not have watched in The White Princess, I can’t remember if I watched that, I know I watched The White Queen. But either way I think the fact I either haven’t seen her previous shows or don’t remember her in them makes her performance better as I don’t remember what she’s been like in other things. But she plays crazy very well, she really does come off as quite crazy. But then again, she is a hitwoman, you probably have to be a little crazy or at least not so caring/maybe a little heartless to be one otherwise you’d cry after killing all of your hits and that wouldn’t be good lol. She definitely seems unhinged and heartless, especially the way she killed Eve’s mate in the club! That was shocking and no one noticed!

I like watching her mess with Eve and their game of cat and mouse go on. Especially now they both know who each other are and that they are basically both hunting each other.

I can’t wait to see how this season ends! And for season 2 as it’s already been renewed! <3

It’s sheer epicness is so exciting to watc <3
